x4freetext: The measurements were performed using
the 1 MV JN Van de Graaff accelerator at the Compact
Accelerator System for Performing Astrophysical
Research at the Sanford Underground Research Facility
The ZrN targets were fabricated by reactive
sputtering of Zr in a nitrogen atmosphere
enriched in 14N. Nominal thicknesses of the targets
were 50 and 100 nm, respectively.The stability of the
targets was continuously monitored during the course
of the experiment by measuring the narrow resonance
at Ep=278 keV. Target degradation was found to be
linearly dependent on the integrated charge.
integrated charge
Gamma rays were observed with a Canberra
coaxial p-type high-purity germanium detector of 130%
relative efficiency.
